#NotSoSecretPoetry

Laundry washed clean,
In a bucket ridden in the dirt, 
What lies unsaid,
Wholly unseen, or ahead.
Stripes of wrath, 
And not one healthy bean.
No water, now left on any scene.
Wash, wash in a river.
Poisoned words of gold & silver.
Horses shiver.
All quiver.
